uk.ac.ebi.ep.mm.app

Class UniprotSaxParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.xml.sax.helpers.DefaultHandler
      • uk.ac.ebi.ep.mm.app.MmSaxParser
        • uk.ac.ebi.ep.mm.app.UniprotSaxParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ContentHandler, DTDHandler, EntityResolver, ErrorHandler, MmParser

    public class UniprotSaxParser
extends MmSaxParser
    UniProt XML parser which takes into account only primary accessions, entry names (IDs), organisms, EC numbers and PDB codes, and indexes/stores them in a mega-map.
    Only enzymes - i.e. entries with an EC number assigned - are considered.
    Author:
    rafa

      • searchMoleculeInChEBI

        protected Entry searchMoleculeInChEBI(String moleculeName)
        Searches a compound name in ChEBI. Please note that if the name does not match exactly any names/synonyms returned by ChEBI, the result will be null.
        Parameters:
        moleculeName - the compound name.
        Returns:
        an entry with a ChEBI ID, or null if not found.
